  <span id="freeText7264591596650332005" style="display:none">Books are made to be reread, says Borges in one of his short stories. I definitely have to reread this oneX maybe in one year, maybe in ten. or maybe one short story a month. short story is not completely accurate. Borges has the power to create whole universes in just a few pages. there are so many motives and themes in this book, it is simply overwhelming. He talks about love, about alterego, about writing, about infinity, about death, about words, about heresy. His erudism is overwhelming, his views about life are so humble and so clear. <br />One need to read such books at least once in a lifetime or once in a while to appreciate the real value of literature. </span>
